      "content": "I can assure you that these institutions are designed to be liquid, but I'll provide some additional information on their withdrawal policies to alleviate your concerns.\n\nAlly, Marcus by Goldman Sachs, and SoFi have relatively straightforward policies regarding emergency withdrawals. None of them lock your money away, but there are some nuances to consider:\n\n* Ally: Ally allows you to withdraw up to 6 withdrawals per month, and each withdrawal is limited to $1,000. If you exceed this limit, you'll be charged a $10 fee for each additional withdrawal.\n* Marcus by Goldman Sachs: Marcus doesn't charge any fees for withdrawals, but you're limited to 6 withdrawals per month. If you exceed this limit, you'll need to wait 30 days before making another withdrawal.\n* SoFi: SoFi allows unlimited withdrawals, but you'll be charged a $10 fee for each withdrawal if you exceed the average daily balance of $1,000 for 30 consecutive days.\n\nIn terms of locking your money away, none of these institutions have a \"lockbox\" policy, where your money is frozen for a certain period. However, they may temporarily restrict your access to your account if they suspect unusual activity or if they need to verify your identity.",
